Johannesburg’s Emergency Management Services (EMS) is assessing the damage caused to homes in Ennerdale, south of Johannesburg, after overnight reports of the suburb being hit by a minor tornado. EMS spokesman Robert Mulaudzi said disaster management officials were checking up to 50 households that had sustained damaged roofs and collapsed walls. Mulaudzi tweeted overnight that three homes had been extensively damaged. Images and videos of the tornado flooded social media overnight‚ showing damaged homes. Search-SA tweeted: "Minor tornado swept through Ennerdale with major damages caused." Wetsi Phutsisi uploaded a video of the tornado swirling over homes. The extent of the damage and any injuries sustained by residents is still being assessed. TMG Digital